The latter article is especially interesting for two reasons. It is a couple of years old, and it specifically mentions nuclear power. <br>
There have been rumors for some time that India had worked on a nuclear rocket called &quot;Surya&quot; (&quot;Sun&quot;), not to be confused with a rumored ICBM of the same name. We discussed this pretty extensively on the old PO board. I even wrote to a former Indian space official, he admitted that such a thing had been &quot;looked into&quot; but very little information was available. I went so far as to suggest that Surya might even be Orion, but a NERVA type device seems more likely. <br>
